reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and holds a lot of shoes
reviews.reviewText: This shoe rack is perfect for what I need it for. It’s sturdy and holds a lot of pairs of shoes. I use to have one of those clipped racks and it was held together with duct tape and kept collapsing. My shoes were just a pile in my closet basically. This is still a relatively cheap rack, but it’s great for what I need it for, sturdy, and holds many shoes! My husband assembled it in less than 5 minutes. Highly recommend if you don’t want to spend a lot of money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Very nice and easy to put together. Even at the smallest size it fits 8 pairs of shoes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble shoe rack is practical expandable.
reviews.reviewText: This shoe rack is very easy to assemble. There are no tools needed, and none included! The metal rods ( I chose the bronze ) just snap together with a push pin holding the the assemble up. This makes it very easy to put together and can be done in less than ten minutes after you read the instructions. However, the fact that the rods are simply pushed together makes the shoe rack overall a bit unsteady. The real issue is today most of the casual shoes and even many of the more dressier shoes do not have a traditional heel, which would hold the shoe on the rack a bit tighter. Most of my shoes have a solid rubberized sole with no heel. All in all, this is a very useful and very easy to assemble shoe rack and is recommended.

reviews.reviewText: The unit arrived with a bent end and some paint coming off. Looks more brown than bronze. Shoes without heels slide off because the rods are round, not square as the one I was replacing. Gets flimsily when fully expanded. The space between rods is over 5" and some shoes fall through, the old one I was replacing, the distance is less than 5".

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A Little Shaky
reviews.reviewText: This shoe rack will hold about 8 pairs of adult-sized shoes at the farthest extension. Smaller-sized kid's shoes would fall through the rails so this rack wouldn't work for them. It is a bit unstable and shaky so I had to push it against a wall to help keep it steady. It should have some kind of clamp to keep the adjustable rails in position. If you knock into it without enough shoes on it to hold it extended, the rails will slide back and forth easily. A clamp would probably make it more steady as well. Good enough for the closet floor where it won't be jostled very often.
The gap between each layer is good for sneakers, flat shoes and NOT boots.
